I'm still sick! Right now I can't remember what its like to be able to breathe and to be able to hear things clearly. Everytime I go to work I get more sick. I think my almost 2 weeks off from work is going to be good for me. I went to the doctor the other day to see what was wrong with me and he didn't know. I got my fist anti-biotic though! The pills are huge and the cough medicine tastes like death. I don't feel like its working but maybe it is?? It's only my second day of taking it. 

Babysitting tonight for Jackson and Ilana. They are cute but I'm just not in the mood to babysit. They have at least 200 DVD's though so hopefully I'll be able to find a good movie to watch when they go to bed! 

Gotta go dry my hair and then leave. 6 days til Spokane! I'm so excited! yay! Pray for NO SNOW in the pass next weekend!

Finals so far have been pretty good. Calculus was interesting and I couldnt tell if I knew how to do the problems or if I was pretending like I knew what I was doing. I dont really care what I got on that one though because I'm all done with that class forever and it doesnt matter anymore. IB Bio 2 and Chemistry were today. Chem was really easy and Bio was pretty easy too. I didnt finish the written part though because I didnt feel good and I just couldnt concentrate anymore. TV production tomorrow.... watching a movie... then running 7 laps in 20 minutes for Raquet Sports. Can't really complain about finals this year. 

Schedule for next semester:
1. TV Production 
2. Health with Oprea
3. Chem with Dr. V
4. IB Bio 2 with Dr. V again!
5. Preschool T.A.
6. Creative Writing with McCombs

Not too tough!

Happy New Year! Its 2005 and we graduate in 2005. Doesnt it seem like it wasnt that long ago when it was 1999 going to 2000 and the whole world was freaking out saying it was gonna be the end of the world. And remember when it was 2001 and we were all starting high school looking up to the seniors thinking they looked so old. I cant believe we are the seniors now and its already almost half way through our senior year. Its such a mixed emotion feeling. Part of me is really excited for college and experiencing new things and going off away from home while the other part of me is scared to death for what next year is gonna bring. New people, new places, new everything! My new years resolution... or at least one of them is to make the rest of this year before college the best it can possibly be! 

New years was fun! I went to Seattle with kk to watch the fireworks at the space needle. I'd say we had the best view in town! We didnt have to stand in the seattle center with the other 20,000 people looking straight up into the sky at the fireworks. We were up on the hill looking over toward the city! It was awesome! Then right after the fireworks were over all hell broke loose in seattle. We were right behind some drunk people driving on the wrong side of the road. Then when there was a car coming at them they swerved over really fast and then stopped in the middle of the road for like 30 seconds. Then on our way to finding the freeway we saw like 5 fire engines, police cars, and ambulances with their sirens on trying to get to somewhere on the freeway. I bet they just love working the new years eve shift!! In all it was a pretty good night! I loved the drive home and the little detour on the way home! It was pretty fun!!!

Time for me to get to bed now. One more day of break tomorrow and then its back to school...meh! I dont know where that break went to but it sure didnt stick around for as long as i would have liked. I dont know if im ready for another month and a half of school! eww! 

Goodnight all!

Love,
Sarah
